SIMPLE: parted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: parted
<hw>part"ed</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧rt"⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Separated; divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Endowed with parts or abilities.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Cleft so that the divisions reach
nearly, but not quite, to the midrib, or the base of the blade; -- said
of a leaf, and used chiefly in composition; <as>as,
three-<ex>parted</ex>, five-<ex>parted</ex>, etc.</as></def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parter</ent>⟦br⟧
